==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Costeaning
<hw>Cos"tean`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The process by which miners
seek to discover metallic lodes. It consist in sinking small pits
through the superficial deposits to the solid rock, and then driving
from one pit to another across the direction of the vein, in such manner
as to cross all the veins between the two pits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Costellate</ent>⟦br⟧
